<img width="640" height="360" src="https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/breachers-640x360.jpg" class="webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image" alt="" style="display: block; margin-bottom: 10px; clear: both; max-width: 100%;" srcset="https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/breachers-640x360.jpg 640w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/breachers-325x183.jpg 325w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/breachers-768x432.jpg 768w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/breachers-747x420.jpg 747w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/breachers-681x383.jpg 681w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /><div style="margin: 5px 5% 10px 5%;"><img src="https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/breachers-341x220.jpg" width="341" height="220" title="Image courtesy Triangle Factory" alt="" /></div><div><p>Triangle Factory announced its squad-based shooter <em>Breachers (2023)</em> was set to arrive on PSVR 2 this month, however the studio says the game will be delayed, as it&#8217;s currently held up in Sony&#8217;s quality assurance (QA) process.</p>
<p><span id="more-114625"></span></p>
<blockquote class="td_quote_box td_box_center"><p><strong>Update (November 28th, 2023)</strong>: Triangle Factory announced Breachers is delayed, as the game is still being checked for QA. There&#8217;s no updated release date yet, however the studio says it will announce it &#8220;soon.&#8221; The full statement follows below, along with the original article:</p></blockquote>
<figure id="attachment_115279" style="width: 1920px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/breachers-delay-psvr-2-1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-115279" src="https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/breachers-delay-psvr-2-1.jpg" alt="" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/breachers-delay-psvr-2-1.jpg 1920w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/breachers-delay-psvr-2-1-125x70.jpg 125w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/breachers-delay-psvr-2-1-320x180.jpg 320w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/breachers-delay-psvr-2-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/breachers-delay-psvr-2-1-640x360.jpg 640w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/breachers-delay-psvr-2-1-747x420.jpg 747w, https://roadtovrlive-5ea0.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/breachers-delay-psvr-2-1-681x383.jpg 681w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" /></a><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Image courtesy Triangle Factory</figcaption></figure>
<p><em><strong>Original Article (October 17th, 2023)</strong></em>: The studio <a href="https://twitter.com/BreachersVR/status/1713910501300998381" target="_blank" rel="noopener">announced the news via X</a> (formerly Twitter), saying the PSVR 2 version will include adaptive trigger support, trophies, and enhanced visuals. It&#8217;s also slated to include crossplay with Quest and SteamVR headsets. Unlike the PC version, the game&#8217;s spectator mode isn&#8217;t coming to PlayStation however.</p>
<p>Inspired by <em>Rainbow Six Siege, Breachers </em>brings some pretty familiar action to the table, letting squads attack or defend weapon in-hand. As Enforcers, rappel and breach through walls, swing through windows and catch your opponents by surprise with stuff like drones, cloaking devices, flashbangs and breaching foam.</p>

<p>As Revolters, user gadgets such as door-blockers, trip mines, static field emitters and proximity sensors to stop the enemy from disarming your bomb.</p>
<p>You can find the game <a href="https://www.oculus.com/experiences/quest/5740397619319389/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">on Quest</a>, <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1922010/Breachers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SteamVR</a>, and Pico headsets, priced at $30. Besdies the November launch window, Triangle Factory hasn&#8217;t mentioned a precise release date yet. In the meantime, you can wishlist the game on PlayStation <a href="https://store.playstation.com/en-us/concept/10008882" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
